# Hub Session Start

Before creating tickets or making code edits for a new request, ensure the active Hub client and project are set for this workspace.

## Session start checklist

1. Run `node tools/hub-workflow-cli.mjs show-session`
2. If no session exists, or the user is working for a different client/project:
   - Run `node tools/hub-workflow-cli.mjs list-clients`
   - **Ask the user which client** this work is for
   - Run `node tools/hub-workflow-cli.mjs list-projects --client-id "<client-uuid>"`
   - **Ask the user which project** under that client
   - Run `node tools/hub-workflow-cli.mjs set-session --client-id "<client-uuid>" --project-id "<project-uuid>"`
3. Confirm session with `show-session` before `create-ticket`

## Rules

- Never guess client or project — always ask when session is missing or unclear
- Match folder context only as a hint; user confirmation wins
- Multiple clients can share the same project name (e.g. two "New Website" projects) — always use ids from `list-projects --client-id`
- `create-ticket` uses the session project when `--project-id` is omitted
- Include active `client_name`, `project_name`, and ids in status updates
- To switch client/project mid-session: `clear-session` then repeat the checklist

## Portable setup (any repo)

Copy from `hub-cursor-kit/` in Appdoers CRM repo, or ensure this repo has:

- `tools/hub-workflow-cli.mjs`
- `tools/hub-ticket-time.mjs`
- `.env.local` with `APPDOERS_HUB_URL` and `APPDOERS_CURSOR_TOKEN`
- Rule files under `.cursor/rules/`

Run `hub-cursor-kit/install.ps1` from the kit to copy everything into a new project.
